x4freetext: double differential cross section over neutron emission
angle and averaged wherever overlap occurred.
No experiments below E(alpha)=4.86 MeV exist.
The spectrum at E(alpha)=4.7MeV was constructed using
1) threshold for break-up neutron is E(alpha)=4.3MeV.
2) intensity for break-up neutrons decreases linearly
to zero from E(alpha)=4.8 to 4.3 MeV.
3) general trend of other curves give the spect.shape.

x4freetext: Gibbons et al. (1965) measured the total neutron
production cross-section for all neutron groups,
including the break-up neutrons. There are some
discrepancies between the present data and those
by Gibbons et al. The correction factor to adjust
the present data to Gibbons et al, varies 0.945
to 1.171 (for alpha energies higher than 6.65 MeV).
